Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.52,0:00:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I started a Duel with the Charlie, owner of Number 7, the card with the strongest luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.15,0:00:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Plus the location is a rampaged monorail which has lost control.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.78,0:00:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If this continues, we'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.20,0:00:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.08,0:00:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s almost time for your surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.21,0:00:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.96,0:00:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t worry, it will be over while you're still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.50,0:00:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.88,0:00:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But my uncle still hasn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.59,0:00:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.60,0:00:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, Yuma. Let our Carnival begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.73,0:00:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha, here I come! My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.98,0:00:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll set a Monster in face-down Defense Position! And set one more card, ending my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.45,0:00:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is he really planning to win with luck alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.91,0:01:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.58,0:01:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Continuous Magic, Trading Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.41,0:01:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start out small. Let me test my luck a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.96,0:01:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card allows me to toss a die once per turn, and if I tossed a six, my current Life will increase five times!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.30,0:01:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, if I get another value, my Life will return to the value prior to activation!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.10,0:01:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if you'll get a six that easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.85,0:01:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. He managed to roll five consecutive sixes in the previous Duel. The odds of the next one being 6 is 1/46656.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.40,0:01:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Behold…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.32,0:01:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s definitely impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.20,0:01:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.54,0:01:47.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Six?! He got it again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.21,0:01:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Five times 4000 is 20000!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.88,0:01:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So long as the sun is round, my luck won't end!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.30,0:02:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! The sun set a long time ago, darn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.10,0:02:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, which means nothing can stop my fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Majestic Jester!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I attack the Monster in face-down Defense Position with Majestic Jester!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.07,0:02:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He attacked with a zero Attack Power Monster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.28,0:02:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Desperate Mime!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.79,0:02:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gogogo Golem’s DEF is 1500. You're the one who’s taking damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.71,0:02:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pity, Yuma. I activate the effect of Majestic Jester!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.42,0:02:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}More{\i0} dice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.42,0:02:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to utilize this extraordinary luck to its fullest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.64,0:02:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Majestic Jester declares an attack, if I tossed a six, it destroys a Monster my opponent controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I got other values, then this card is destroyed and says his goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.10,0:02:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The probability of another consecutive six is 1/129936.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.78,0:02:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Like heck he will!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.36,0:02:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.15,0:03:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.50,0:03:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.58,0:03:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.75,0:03:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo! I destroy Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.38,0:03:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card, and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.85,0:03:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this continues, we will…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.27,0:03:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fret not! We're standing next to the world's luckiest good luck charm, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.55,0:03:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As I get closer, I stretch my hand out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.22,0:03:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}towards that shining light leading towards tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.44,0:03:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I dream of a world that expands from my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.28,0:04:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I haven't a clue of where things like dreams and hopes are at.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.79,0:04:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I run looking for it, I still can't seem to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.25,0:04:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder if I have fallen into a gap of truth and lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.75,0:04:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even so, our grand tale has yet to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.97,0:04:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's move on towards tomorrow, \Neven if our road begins to fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.22,0:04:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will jump forward, before all my\N strength completely drains.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.90,0:04:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The closer I get, the further it becomes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.48,0:04:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that truth that I must seize.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.65,0:04:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's to find hope that we desire from a future unseen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.82,0:04:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With a heart stronger than anyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.62,0:04:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll learn to keep running up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.91,0:04:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With the strength to win any battle, \Ndespite just how weak I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.63,0:04:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My purpose is to find,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.63,0:04:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}with these invaluable friends of mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.63,0:05:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The future of the world expanding\N from my feet with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.42,0:05:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charlie...! Charlie!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.59,0:05:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He completely disappeared after that, and no one knew where he went. That idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.14,0:05:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(485,504)}"Number 32: The Insurmountable Luck!\N Number 7, Lucky Stripes!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.27,0:05:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.23,0:05:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Gagaga Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.94,0:05:46.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll win with luck as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.15,0:05:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Magic Card, Monster Slot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.24,0:05:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Banish one Monster in my Graveyard who has same level as Gagaga Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I card allows me to draw one card from my deck, if the drawn Monster has same level as those 2 Monsters, I can special summon it to my field!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if it doesn’t match, the drawn Monster and targeted card will be Banished!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.56,0:06:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're taking too many risks!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.02,0:06:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are so annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.39,0:06:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I get it, I'll have enough materials for a Rank 4 Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you still don’t understand. I already absorbed your luck, so there's nothing left for you to use!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.69,0:06:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break! C'mon, my good fortune!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.37,0:06:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.79,0:06:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way~!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.38,0:06:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you! You can't surpass my luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.55,0:06:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn! I end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this continues, our chances of defeating him will trickle down to zero percent...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.72,0:06:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?! What the heck are you going on about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.10,0:06:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get it, Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.06,0:07:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The luck attached to my cards is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.06,0:07:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father, Kazuma-{\i1}san{\i0}, was once my idol who greatly inspired me. I used to think he has everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.24,0:07:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there was one thing he lacked, and that was luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.70,0:07:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only he had slightly better luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It had nothing to do with luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.50,0:07:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are some critical moments in a person's life where they can't afford to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.75,0:07:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right, even it means they have to win by relying on luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come! My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.10,0:07:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, here goes! The Continuous Magic, Trade Game! If I hit the jack pot, my Life will increase 5 fold!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.94,0:07:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won’t come again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.94,0:07:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He rolled a six!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.61,0:07:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Life is Carnival! Now my Life is 100000!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.91,0:08:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,100000 Life?? How can we ever beat that Life?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.75,0:08:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card, Release Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By releasing one Monster on my field, I can Special Summon one Monster with the same level!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.63,0:08:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I release the Level One Majestic Jester, and Special Summon Diceslot Seven with the same level!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.18,0:08:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate the Magic Card, Monster Slot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! It's the same as me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.73,0:08:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right. What will happen if I do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.11,0:08:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I target the Level One Diceslot Seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remove the Level One Majestic Jester from my Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.54,0:08:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if I draw a Level One Monster, I can Special Summon that Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.01,0:08:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, here it comes! I Special Summon Diceslot Seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.60,0:09:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.72,0:09:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, I Normal Summon the third Diceslot Seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.90,0:09:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in trouble, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.36,0:09:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Diceslot Seven can raise its level according tot the tossed value until the End Phase!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.78,0:09:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, give me three sixes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.17,0:09:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The odds of getting three sixes is 1/362790000!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.00,0:09:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it! I don’t want to hear that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.22,0:09:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s finish this once and for all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.76,0:09:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something so unreal... actually happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.81,0:09:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The level of all three Diceslot Sevens goes from one to seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.65,0:09:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay the three Level Seven Diceslot Sevens!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.57,0:10:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I build the Overlay Network with the three Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.41,0:10:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth! Number 7! Lucky Stripe!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.75,0:10:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.71,0:10:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Number!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.42,0:10:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's here, here, here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.13,0:10:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,LIFE IS CARNIVAL!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.14,0:10:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.31,0:10:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I said, as long as the sun remains as one, whole unit...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.40,0:10:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...my good fortune won’t end!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.70,0:10:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kotori-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akari-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.45,0:10:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen carefully, there's only five minutes left before this monorail reaches its destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.25,0:10:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.96,0:10:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, I'll handle it somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.80,0:11:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma! We're close to the destination!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.09,0:11:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.80,0:11:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.43,0:11:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Lucky Stripe’s effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.18,0:11:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this Monster battles, by detaching one Overlay Unit, I roll a die!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.85,0:11:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And after the battle concludes, Lucky Stripe's Attack Power will increase by its original Attack Power times the number rolled on the die.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.92,0:11:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s six! Lucky Stripe’s original Attack Power is 700, so times six, it’s 4200!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.17,0:11:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,4200?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.97,0:11:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I attack you directly with Lucky Stripe!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.01,0:11:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Super Lucky Nova!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.39,0:11:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, use the Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.93,0:11:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.18,0:11:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap Card, open! Clever Scheme!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.06,0:11:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm about to receive a direct attack, by sending one Monster Card from my hand to the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.15,0:12:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this card reduces the Battle Damage equal to the Attack of the sent Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.90,0:12:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I send Zubaba Knight to the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.50,0:12:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, a Trap Card? Impressive indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.09,0:12:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.96,0:12:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.13,0:12:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, can't you do anything?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If his fortune really is flawless, then there really is nothing we can do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.51,0:12:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can’t be serious…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.85,0:12:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Yuma! What are you sulking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.73,0:12:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.39,0:12:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akari?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.69,0:12:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charlie! Just you wait! I will get there to give you a good beating!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.86,0:12:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're as passionate as ever! If it's a kiss you're after, I'd be glad to oblige!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.20,0:12:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, I guess you were crushed by Lucky Stripe, the card Charlie stole, Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to tell you something regarding that card!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.37,0:12:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the sun splits in two, its power will be carried away with the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.21,0:13:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.42,0:13:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a rumor that talks about how to take the luck away from that card.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.88,0:13:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the luck away?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I've been saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.59,0:13:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Life is Carnival!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.97,0:13:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means my luck won't disappear as long as the sun is round and whole!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.35,0:13:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two suns...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.31,0:13:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's what makes this card's fortune absolute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.86,0:13:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don’t have much time left!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.57,0:13:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, Yuma. It's probably about the right time for you to be surrendering.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.53,0:13:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if! I... I'll never give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.46,0:13:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.29,0:13:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Ganbara Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a Level Four Monster is Summoned successfully, I can Special summon Shadow Lizard from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.93,0:13:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I overlay the Level Four Shadow Lizard and Ganbara Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.81,0:13:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I build the Overlay Network with these two Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.90,0:14:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.86,0:14:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Number 39!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.44,0:14:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.57,0:14:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Aspiring Emperor - Hope to attack Lucky Seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.33,0:14:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Permanent Trap, activate! Dice Crisis!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.79,0:14:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By tossing a die, if I get a six, this card makes the Attack Power of one Monster my opponent controls zero! I then gain control of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.80,0:14:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ole!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.38,0:14:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won’t show up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don’t show up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.01,0:14:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to disappoint. I got a six again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.73,0:14:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Hope belongs to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.94,0:14:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.53,0:14:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.37,0:14:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're pretty close to the final stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.03,0:15:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to finish to this Duel. After all, you can’t win anyway. Everything is fruitless in front of my strong luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.00,0:15:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pissing me off with this “luck, luck” talk!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.84,0:15:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter whether you have luck or not! All that matters is that a person tries their best in a fight! That's how Dueling should be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.30,0:15:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like my Dad taught me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.93,0:15:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.60,0:15:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Dad never relied on luck! He always opened the path with his own strength! And I'll do the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.90,0:15:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.94,0:15:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.78,0:15:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. Then allow mew to finish this once and for all. My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.49,0:15:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.45,0:15:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.16,0:15:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! Trap Card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.20,0:15:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Command of Sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.83,0:15:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When there is a Light-Attribute Warrior-Type Monster on my side of field, I can activate this effect in my opponent’s Draw Phase!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.92,0:15:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now draw your card!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the drawn card is a magic or trap, I can either destroy the drawn card, or destroy one Magic or Trap card on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.64,0:16:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that’s so? Your goal is to destroy Dice Crisis, and get Hope back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.36,0:16:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw it, Charlie!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.99,0:16:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The card I drew is Sun’s Scale!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.20,0:16:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By tossing a die once per turn, if I get a six, all Monsters on my opponent’s field will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.04,0:16:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even you get back your Hope, my victory won’t change! As long as the sun is still round!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.25,0:16:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I target Dice Crisis…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.42,0:16:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, the sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.89,0:16:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Split the sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.35,0:16:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.72,0:16:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as the sun is round and whole...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! So you mean...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.44,0:16:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t believe such thing could happen in a Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.69,0:16:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the effect of Command of Sword, the selected warrior, Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.07,0:16:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut the sun from the Magic Card, the Scale of Sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.41,0:16:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It can't be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.28,0:17:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.58,0:17:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope Sword Slash!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.34,0:17:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun... became two!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.31,0:17:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! The luck…really…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.35,0:17:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That light is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.06,0:17:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t tell me the card’s power…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.44,0:17:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could that happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.86,0:17:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Scale of Sun was destroyed, you will receive 500 points of damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.04,0:17:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can my luck disappear?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.33,0:17:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Trade Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.83,0:17:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I roll a six, my Life will increase 5 fold! Otherwise it will return to its original value.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.18,0:18:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.85,0:18:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So my fortune... really did vanish?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.77,0:18:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.36,0:18:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, do it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.82,0:18:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, my turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.28,0:18:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card, Come Back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.99,0:18:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will recover one of my Monsters on my opponent’s field!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.83,0:18:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back, my Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.09,0:18:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.84,0:18:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chaos Xyz Change!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.26,0:18:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now show your self, Chaos Numbers 39!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The messenger who used the power of Hope to turn chaos into light! Aspiring Emperor - Hope Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.73,0:18:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope Ray…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.23,0:18:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Aspiring Emperor - Hope Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.65,0:19:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one Overlay Unit, it gains 500 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.07,0:19:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Overlay Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.41,0:19:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And for every Overlay Unit detached, the opponent’s Monster’s Attack Power will decrease by 1000!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.46,0:19:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! I attack Lucky Stripe with Aspiring Emperor - Hope Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.67,0:19:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope Sword Chaos Slash!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.32,0:19:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.03,0:19:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.07,0:19:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The final stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.53,0:19:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can’t make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.04,0:19:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.50,0:19:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akari's gonna bring it to ya!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.23,0:20:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.73,0:20:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are two of you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.94,0:20:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.56,0:20:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.53,0:20:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, where’s Charlie?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.61,0:20:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My luck… My luck has disappeared…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.58,0:20:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry, Mayumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.70,0:20:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.58,0:20:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A..Akari!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.62,0:20:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this woman named Mayumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.59,0:20:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.34,0:20:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.05,0:20:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.51,0:20:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought those magic words with me! "Bring it to 'em", Mayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it to 'em?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.43,0:20:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, do your best!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.14,0:20:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.15,0:21:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, I will give this card to you as your lucky charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.03,0:21:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks! I'll bring it to 'em and do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.12,0:21:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The card...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.08,0:21:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe its luck came back when it changed ownership!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.46,0:21:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s going to be alright, the surgery will definitely be a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.55,0:21:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that girl's surgery comes with great difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.01,0:21:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I... wanted to give my luck to her... along with that card.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.68,0:21:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charlie…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.06,0:21:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Even so, there was no need to do something like-\N - Akari!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.85,0:21:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell Yuma for me that, "You're a splendid successor to Kazuma-{\i1}san{\i0}'s spirit of bringin' it to 'em."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.36,0:21:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.95,0:21:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your help, Akari.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.41,0:21:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch, that hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.67,0:22:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later! I hope you can dress a bit more casual the next time we meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.17,0:22:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! The day's finally over!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.43,0:22:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup! I'm hungry now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.30,0:22:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will she really return the Number to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.35,0:22:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.47,0:22:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I think we need to be more concerned about this! Hey! Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.14,0:22:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someone gave me some water.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.68,0:22:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So I was able to paint a rainbow with ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.36,0:22:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to become someone perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.94,0:22:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it's very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.32,0:22:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even with me suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.91,0:22:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't seem to grasp victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.75,0:22:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to bloom!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.21,0:23:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I must be having some kind of weird dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.13,0:23:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But If I must fulfill this,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.67,0:23:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then I don't mind being laughed at for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.63,0:23:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Since it's because your limits are decided on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.85,0:23:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll show it, overcoming it to tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.85,0:23:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah, I'm aiming for the big blue sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.27,0:23:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For all of its glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.00,0:23:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Freesia of Desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.58,0:23:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All of those countless flower petals
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.41,0:23:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They came at the expense of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.08,0:23:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}me being able to reach those heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.19,0:23:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah, even though I lost my way today,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.42,0:23:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I still yearn for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.09,0:23:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That Freesia of Desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.99,0:23:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the guy Shark's trying to get revenge on, IV!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.66,0:23:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He started a Duel with Tetsuo and the class rep!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.66,0:23:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.99,0:24:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Tag Duel of Hell! The Evil Hero, IV"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.29,0:24:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!
